        <p class="truth__industry-tagline">The truth about tips</p>
      </div>

      <div class="truth__columns">
        <!-- Driver -->
        <div class="truth__col">
          <h4 class="truth__col-title">
            <span class="truth__role-icon">👨‍✈️</span> For the driver
          </h4>
          <ol class="truth__list">
            <li>
              <strong>Algorithmic manipulation of hourly income</strong>
              <span>When a customer leaves a tip, the algorithm reduces or stops trip assignments, assuming the driver has already reached the "ideal" hourly income. This effectively turns the driver into an hourly employee, without transparency and without labor rights.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Elimination of the real meaning of tipping</strong>
              <span>The tip stops being an extra income from gratitude and becomes a variable controlled by the platform to adjust the driver's earnings.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Anticipated algorithmic manipulation</strong>
              <span>Platforms use the tip placed in advance to predict and limit the driver's income, ensuring they do not "exceed" the designed hourly earnings.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Emotional instability for the driver</strong>
              <span>The driver lives in uncertainty, not knowing whether they will receive the full tip, whether it will be reduced, or whether it will be delayed by the system.</span>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <!-- Customer -->
        <div class="truth__col">
          <h4 class="truth__col-title">
            <span class="truth__role-icon">👤</span> For the customer
          </h4>
          <ol class="truth__list">
            <li>
              <strong>Absurd pressure on the customer</strong>
              <span>In many cases, customers are forced to place the tip before the service, distorting the real intention of thanking for good work.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Uncertainty about whether the driver will actually receive the promised tip</strong>
              <span>Many customers do not know if the tip is withheld, adjusted, or reduced after it has been sent.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>A feeling of obligation instead of gratitude</strong>
              <span>Customers feel that if they don't leave a tip, they are considered "bad users," not because of the service, but because of interface pressure.</span>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══════════════ FOOD SERVICE ═══════════════ -->
    <div class="truth__industry anim-rise" style="animation-range: entry 0% cover 25%">
      <div class="truth__industry-head">
        <span class="truth__emoji" aria-hidden="true">🍽️</span>
