        <p class="truth__industry-tagline">The truth about tips</p>
      </div>

      <div class="truth__columns">
        <!-- Client -->
        <div class="truth__col">
          <h4 class="truth__col-title">
            <span class="truth__role-icon">👤</span> Client
          </h4>
          <ol class="truth__list">
            <li>
              <strong>Low base salaries depending on tips</strong>
              <span>They feel responsible for completing a salary that should be paid by the restaurant.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Retention or theft of tips by the restaurant</strong>
              <span>The client believes they helped the waiter, but in reality the company keeps a percentage.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Unfair tip distribution (poorly managed tip pooling)</strong>
              <span>Their tips do not reach the waiter who attended them.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Tipflation (tip inflation)</strong>
              <span>Screens suggest increasingly higher tips (20–30% or more). They feel pressured to pay higher amounts even if the service was basic.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Social pressure and manipulation at the point of payment</strong>
              <span>The tablet turns towards them and makes them feel obligated to leave a tip. Embarrassment or discomfort if they do not want to tip or want to leave less.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Deterioration of gratitude</strong>
              <span>Gratitude stops being a natural expression and becomes an uncomfortable obligation.</span>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <!-- Restaurant Staff -->
        <div class="truth__col">
          <h4 class="truth__col-title">
            <span class="truth__role-icon">👩‍🍳👨‍🍳</span> Restaurant Staff
          </h4>
          <ol class="truth__list">
            <li>
              <strong>Low base salaries depending on tips</strong>
              <span>They live with financial anxiety and depend on external factors: weather, traffic, customer mood, etc.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Retention or theft of tips by the restaurant</strong>
              <span>They lose legitimate income that they should receive as part of their work.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Unfair tip distribution (poorly managed tip pooling)</strong>
              <span>They share the tip with staff who sometimes do not contribute to the direct service, or even with management.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Tipflation (tip inflation)</strong>
              <span>Although suggested percentages rise, their income does not necessarily increase, because many clients react by reducing or avoiding tipping.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Social pressure and manipulation at the point of payment</strong>
              <span>They are judged or pointed out according to the tip each client leaves, affecting the work environment.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Deterioration of gratitude</strong>
              <span>Gratitude loses its real value and becomes a metric that determines their income, not an authentic human gesture.</span>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </div>
